startGuidance.heading = Calculate Stamp Duty Land Tax (SDLT)
startGuidance.content.l1 = This calculator can be used for property purchases that are:
startGuidance.bullet.b1 = for first-time buyers
startGuidance.bullet.b2 = replacing main residence
startGuidance.bullet.b3 = additional property
startGuidance.bullet.b4 = residential or non-residential
startGuidance.bullet.b5 = freehold or leasehold
startGuidance.bullet.b6 = for non-UK residents purchasing residential property
startGuidance.content.l2 = The calculator will work out the SDLT payable for most transactions. You should
startGuidance.content.l3 = if you are uncertain about how SDLT applies to your purchase or if you believe it may qualify for a relief.
startGuidance.content.l4 = There are
startGuidance.content.l5 = purchasing residential property for more than £500,000.


