section.sharedOwnership = Shared ownership scheme
sharedOwnership.heading = Are you buying the property through a shared ownership scheme?
sharedOwnership.error.required = Select ''Yes'' or ''No''
sharedOwnership.p1 = The scheme must be operated by an approved qualifying body, like a housing association or local authority.

currentValue.heading = What is the market value of the property?
currentValue.p1 = This means the market value at the time of purchase. If the maximum share of the property ultimately obtainable is less than 100%, enter the value of that percentage.
currentValue.error.required = Select a value
currentValue.atOrBelowThreshold = £{0} or less
currentValue.aboveThreshold = More than £{0}
currentValue.atOrBelowThreshold.hint = May qualify for First Time Buyers Relief.

marketValue.heading = Do you want to pay SDLT on the market value or only on the percentage of the property you are buying?
marketValue.p1 = You can choose to pay SDLT on the market value of the property. This is known as a ‘market value election’.
marketValue.details.title = How does this work?
marketValue.details.d1.p1 = First Time Buyers Relief
marketValue.details.d1.p2 = will be applied to the SDLT on:
marketValue.details.d1.b1 = the market value of the property, or
marketValue.details.d1.b2 = on the market value of the share of the property that is ultimately obtainable under the scheme
marketValue.details.d1.p3 = No further SDLT will be due if you purchase further shares in the property or acquire the property outright.
marketValue.p2 = Alternatively you can choose to pay SDLT on the amount you are paying for your initial purchase.
marketValue.details.d2.p1 = If you pay SDLT in stages, your First Time Buyers Relief will only be applied to the initial payment you make, including any rental payments.
marketValue.details.d2.p2 = Further payments towards your property purchase made at a later stage may be liable to SDLT which could add up to a higher or lower total amount payable than the ‘market value election’ option. First Time Buyers Relief is not available against those further payments.
marketValue.details.d2.p3 = However if your total share in the property is never more than 80%, then you will not be liable for any further SDLT.
marketValue.PayUpfront = Pay SDLT up front by making a market value election
marketValue.PayInStages = Pay SDLT in stages
